    <div class="blogPost web_exclusive_post last">
      <div class="postTitle">
        <h5 class="subheader"><a href="http://www.democracynow.org/blog/2015/4/2/hate_doesn_t_pay" data-clicky-href="#widget/blog/columns_&amp;_articles" data-clicky-title="Widget: Blog Columns &amp; Articles Link">Hate Doesn’t Pay</a>
        </h5>
      </div>
        <div class="postImage" id="blogImage">
          <a href="http://www.democracynow.org/blog/2015/4/2/hate_doesn_t_pay"><img alt="Amys_column_default_640x360_2014" src="/images/blog_posts/31/27231/medium/amys_column_default_640x360_2014.jpg?201503121638" /></a>
        </div>
      <div class="postSummary">
        <p><strong>By Amy Goodman with Denis Moynihan</strong><br />
Indiana certainly doesn’t want to be remembered for being a bastion of hatred. So why did Indiana Gov. Mike Pence legalize a new wave of intolerance by signing into law Indiana’s controversial “Religious Freedom Restoration Act” (<span class="caps">RFRA</span>)?</p>
      </div>


